  "body": "### User Story\r\n\r\nAs User when I open a DApp profile I want to be able to scroll to see the whole page.\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n*Summary*: When the a DApp is opened from the \"Discover\" tab is open and you are looking at the whole view, if the DApp has a long \"Description\" then this can lead to the URL being below the screen and a scroill view is not implimented here it seems. See screenshot -> http://share.xctest.io/TYsTnB\r\n\r\nNOTE: \"Dynamic Type\" (iOS system text size) could also play a part in this issue occuring.\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nWhole page should be scrollable if loading below the view.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nScroll view not implimented.\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n- Open Status\r\n- Sign in\r\n- Open \"Discover\" tab\r\n- Oen Melonport\r\n- URL isn't 100% visible\r\n- \r\n### Solution\r\n*Summary*: \r\n\r\n- [ ] ...\r\n- [ ] ...\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n\r\n* Status version: 0.9.12\r\n\r\n* Operating System: iOS 11.2 iPhone SE\r\n\r\n#### Logs\r\n\r\nn/a",
